    http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/profile/v0

    ValueWithAttributes LoyaltyProgram

      • http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/profile/v0:LoyaltyProgram

      • Description

        Identifies a membership or loyalty program offered by the company by name of the program.
        Additional Documentation 
        Type Value
        Implementers Assigned XSD Type: {http://chameleon.anonymous/ns}StringLength0to32

    • Example XML

      <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>

<LoyaltyProgram codeContext="I am a tiny string." id="loyaltyProgram_1" loyaltyLevel="I am a tiny string." primaryInd="true" programCode="I am a tiny string." singleVendorIndGroupInd="true" xmlns="http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/profile/v0"/>

      Example JSON

      {
  "LoyaltyProgram" : {
    "value" : null,
    "programCode" : "I am a tiny string.",
    "loyaltyLevel" : "I am a tiny string.",
    "id" : "loyaltyProgram_1",
    "codeContext" : "I am a tiny string.",
    "primaryInd" : true,
    "singleVendorIndGroupInd" : true
  }
}

      • Attribute Summary

        Attributes 
        Name Description
        programCode
        Identification of the loyalty program by code.
        Details
        Type http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v0:Code
        Example Value I am a tiny string.
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        loyaltyLevel
        Indicates special privileges in program assigned to individual.
        Details
        Type http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v0:String_Tiny
        Example Value I am a tiny string.
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        id
        A unique reference for a loyalty program within this message.
        Details
        Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema:ID
        Example Value loyaltyProgram_1
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1

      • Indicator Summary

        Indicators 
        Name Description
        primaryInd
        When true, indicates this is the primary loyalty program and when absent or false, indicates this is not the primary loyalty program.
        singleVendorIndGroupInd
        Present and true Indicates the program is part of an alliance, otherwise it is a single vendor.
